<doc id="368730" wikidata="Q147897" url="?curid=368730" title="Nothoscordum">
<text>Nothoscordum is a genus of New World plants in the onion tribe within the Amaryllis family. It is probably paraphyletic. The genus is native to North, Central and South America, though a few species have become naturalized in various parts of the Old World.

== Species ==
&quot;Plants of the World Online&quot; accepts 91 species, although other authorities suggest only 20.
# &quot;Nothoscordum achalense&quot; - Córdoba in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum albitractum&quot; - Jujuy in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum altillanense&quot; - La Rioja in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum andicola&quot; - Peru, Bolivia, northern Chile, northern Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum aparadense&quot; - Santa Catarina in Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum arenarium&quot; - northern Argentina, Uruguay
# &quot;Nothoscordum auratum&quot; - Uruguay
# &quot;Nothoscordum bahiense&quot; - Bahia in Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum balaenense&quot; - Uruguay
# &quot;Nothoscordum basalticum&quot; - Corrientes in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum bivalve&quot; - southern half of United States from California to Virginia, Mexico, Colombia, Peru, Argentina, Chile, Uruguay
# &quot;Nothoscordum boliviense&quot; - Bolivia, northern Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum bonariense&quot; - northern Argentina, Uruguay, southern Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum × borbonicum&quot; - northern Argentina&quot; (N. entrerianum × N. gracile)&quot;
# &quot;Nothoscordum calcaense&quot; - Peru
# &quot;Nothoscordum calderense&quot; - Salta in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum cambarense&quot; - Rio Grande do Sul in Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum capivarinum&quot; - Paraná in Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum carambolense&quot; - Corrientes in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum catharinense&quot; - Santa Catarina in Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum clevelandicum&quot; - Paraná in Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum collinum&quot; - Rio Grande do Sul in Brazil 
# &quot;Nothoscordum conostylum&quot; - Entre Ríos in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum correntinum&quot; - Corrientes in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum curvipes&quot; - Paraná in Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum cuyanum&quot; - San Juan + Mendoza in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum demissum&quot; - Cusco in Peru
# &quot;Nothoscordum dialystemon&quot; – Rio Grande do Sul in southern Brazil to Uruguay and northeastern Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum dynamiandrum&quot; - Jujuy in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum empedradense&quot; - Corrientes in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum entrerianum&quot; - Entre Ríos in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum exile&quot; - Paraná in Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum famatinense&quot; - La Rioja in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum felipponei&quot; – Uruguay and northern Buenos Aires Province in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum gaudichaudianum&quot; - Uruguay, Entre Ríos in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum gibbatum&quot; – Santa Catarina state in Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum glareosum&quot; - Corrientes in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum gracile&quot; - widespread from southern Mexico to Chile; naturalized in southeastern United States, California, and scattered locations in Europe, Asia, Africa, Australia, and various oceanic islands
# &quot;Nothoscordum gracilipes&quot; - southern Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum hirtellum&quot; – southern Brazil, northeastern Argentina, and Uruguay
# &quot;Nothoscordum ibiramense&quot; - Santa Catarina in southern Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum ineanum&quot; - Chaco in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum inundatum&quot; - Corrientes in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum itapetinga&quot; – São Paulo state in Brazil
# &quot;Nothoscordum ipacarainum&quot; - Paraguay
# &quot;Nothoscordum itatiense&quot; - Corrientes in Argentina
# &quot;Nothoscordum jaibanum&quot; - Minas Gerais in Brazil
